dinelli）表示格雷发现了拍犯罪片的合适配方：“让一切动起来，在线索间开发出很漂亮的引线，偶尔折腾出惊喜，潇洒的派头绝配<ref>{{cite news |title=Rip–off artistry |first=Mick |last=LaSalle |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2003/05/30/DD270386.DTL&type=movies |work=San Francisco Chronicle |publisher=Hearst Communications, Inc |date=2003-05-30 |accessdate=2008-09-13 |archive-date=2008-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080618062132/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2003%2F05%2F30%2FDD270386.DTL&type=movies |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.reelviews.net/movies/i/italian_job.html |title=Review: The Italian Job (2003) |author=Berardinelli, James |date=2003-05-27 |work=ReelViews.net |accessdate=2008-10-09 |archive-date=2008-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516102502/http://www.reelviews.net/movies/i/italian_job.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”《[[综艺_(杂志)|综艺]]》的罗伯特·克勒（Robert Koehler）将影片与另一部犯罪题材电影《[[鬼计神偷|鬼计神偷]]》（2001年）做比较，后者[[爱德华·诺顿|爱德华·诺顿]]扮演了类似的角色<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.variety.com/index.asp?layout=review&reviewid=VE1117920874 |title=The Italian Job |last=Koehler |first=Robert |date=2003-05-26 |work=Variety |publisher=Reed Business Information |accessdate=2008-09-13}}</ref>。

